<subSubSection id="C33A651A98115A13DADCFD21D60DFC21" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F369198115A13DADCFD21D761FCEE" blockId="13.[189,1399,682,782]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098115A13DADCFD21D390FD24" author="Happold" box="[189,389,682,708]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="245 - 247" refId="ref262747" refString="Happold M. 2013 a. Epomophorus labiatus Little Epauletted Fruit Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 245 - 247. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="a">Happold (2013a)</bibRefCitation>
followed 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098115A13DB9CFD21D157FD24" author="Claessen &amp; De Vree" box="[509,834,682,708]" firstAuthor="Claessen" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="209 - 238" refId="ref258380" refString="Claessen C. J. &amp; De Vree F. 1991. Systematic and taxonomic notes on the Epomophorus anuruslabiatus-minor complex with the description of a new species (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Pteropodidae). Senckenbergiana biologica 71 (4 / 6): 209 - 238." type="journal article" year="1991">Claessen &amp; De Vree (1991)</bibRefCitation>
in considering 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298115A13D999FD20D62BFD24" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1880" box="[1016,1086,683,708]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398115A13D999FD20D62BFD24" box="[1016,1086,683,708]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298115A13DADCFD44D3DCFD09" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1837" box="[189,457,719,745]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labiatus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398115A13DADCFD44D3DCFD09" box="[189,457,719,745]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Epomophorus labiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. She also pointed out that 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098115A13D964FD44D1C7FD09" author="Bergmans" box="[773,978,719,745]" firstAuthor="Bergmans" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="11 - 90" refId="ref257500" refString="Bergmans W. 1997. Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). 5. The genera Lissonycteris Andersen, 1913, Myonycteris Matschie, 1899 and Megaloglossus Pagenstecher, 1885; General remarks and conclusions; annex: Key to all species. Beaufortia 47 (2): 11 - 90. Available from http: // www. repository. naturalis. nl / document / 548609 [accessed 29 Nov. 2017]." type="journal article" year="1997">Bergmans (1997)</bibRefCitation>
was strongly opposed to this, as he pointed out a number errors concerning the 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298115A13D8DEFD7ED12AFCEE" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1837" box="[703,831,756,782]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Epomophorus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="labiatus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398115A13D8DEFD7ED12AFCEE" box="[703,831,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. labiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens used by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098115A13DE48FD7FD765FCEE" author="Claessen &amp; De Vree" box="[1065,1392,756,782]" firstAuthor="Claessen" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="209 - 238" refId="ref258380" refString="Claessen C. J. &amp; De Vree F. 1991. Systematic and taxonomic notes on the Epomophorus anuruslabiatus-minor complex with the description of a new species (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Pteropodidae). Senckenbergiana biologica 71 (4 / 6): 209 - 238." type="journal article" year="1991">Claessen &amp; De Vree (1991)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F369198115A13DADCFCBCD60DFC21" blockId="13.[189,1399,823,961]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The distribution map shows that the specimens from the eastern part from the 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198115A13DE11FCBCD6B9FCB1" box="[1136,1196,823,849]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">DRC</collectingCountry>
fit well with the major (eastern African) distribution area of the species. The specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198115A13DE22FCD7D684FC96" box="[1091,1169,860,886]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Congo</collectingCountry>
da Lemba (RMCA 408a, a juvenile male) does seem to fit with a potential distribution along the Angolan coast, which, however, is not yet supported by material from that country (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098115A13D9E7FC2DD619FC21" author="ACR" box="[902,1036,934,961]" firstAuthor="ACR" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" refId="ref254905" refString="ACR. 2016. African Chiroptera Report. AfricanBats, Pretoria. Available from http: // www. africanbats. org / index. php / publications / africa-chiroptera-report [accessed 28 Sep. 2017]." type="url" year="2016">ACR 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
